comments: This melody was first published in "The Petrie Collection of Ancient Music of Ireland" by George Petrie. It didn't have a title at that time. There are different theories about the origin of this song, but it is assumed Jane Ross copied the melody from a fiddler, possibly called Jimmy McCurry, around 1851. A jazzy Earle Hagen arrangement of "Danny Boy" was used as theme song in the "Danny Thomas Show" (titled "Make Room for Daddy" for its first three seasons. This was an American sitcom that ran from 1953 to 1957 on ABC and from 1957 to 1964 on CBS.

As Ritchie said on the mudcat forum: We all were allowed by our regular recording companies to be on this album if our names were not given. name: Rejoicing in Our Covenant Engagements to God 2 Chron. XV. 15.
comments: The text was written by Philip Doddridge (1702-1751). His hymns were produced in the 1730′s and 1740′s, with perhaps a few around 1750, but very few were published during his lifetime, having been circulated only in manuscript. However, in 1755, four years after his death, a collection of them was made and printed by his friend Job Orton, and "O Happy Day," under the heading "Rejoicing in our Covenant engagements to God (2 Chron. 15:15)," was first included in it.
